### Validation
- All CAS writes go through runmanifest.WriteManifestTree → manifest.Validate each
  step → manifest_version stays 2 (no gates) and every snapshot is round-trippable
  via ParseJSON. No new manifest fields → defect #5 (absent/null/empty round-trip)
  is structurally avoided.
- run_id validated via runmanifest.IsValidRunID before any git call.
- Generated git_sha = HEAD (real committed OID) so worktree.Checkout (used by
  replay) always resolves; --git-sha validated via existing validateGitSHA.
- Reject empty workflow / missing runner / undefined seat name / resume-of-complete
  run / resume-of-missing run with clear errors.
- Reserved workflow names (gate round 1, opus): `show` and `list` are valid
  `[a-z0-9-]` names but are shadowed by the `run` subcommands, so `etude run show`
  routes to the subcommand. Reject a workflow argument named `show` or `list` with a
  clear "reserved name" error rather than silently mis-dispatching.
- Forward-replay flag semantics (gate round 1, opus): in 1-arg `etude replay <run>`
  (forward) mode, the single-stage-only flags (`--record`, producer overrides,
  `--output`) are ERRORED with a clear message (they apply only to single-stage
  replay); only forward-relevant flags are honored. Document this one-line decision.
- Empty/no-commit repo edge (gate round 1, opus): `runGitSHA = HEAD` requires a real
  committed OID; emit a clear error when the repo has no commits instead of letting
  worktree.Checkout fail opaquely.

### Test plan (incl. AC proofs)
Hermetic deterministic runner: a tiny committed shell script (e.g.
`testdata/echo-runner.sh`) that reads ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR/* and writes a
deterministic transform to ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE — NO LLM, NO network. A 3-stage
deterministic workflow (a→b→c, all roles chained) drives the proofs.
- AC1 live + mid-run show: run the 3-stage workflow; assert run ref exists and
  manifest grows commit-by-commit (rev-list count increments per stage). Mid-run
  inspectability proved by pausing the runner (a stage script that blocks on a
  fifo/sentinel) and asserting `etude run show <id>` lists already-captured stages
  while a later stage is still pending. Normalize volatile fields (run_id,
  timestamps, git_sha, artifact shas) before golden compare.
- AC2 forward replay: `etude replay <id>` (no stage) re-executes a→b→c forward;
  assert each stage re-runs in order and outputs match the deterministic capture
  (exact, since runner is deterministic + inputs are content-addressed). Use the
  StubRunner/exec path that EXISTS; normalize volatile fields.
- AC3 resume: a workflow whose stage b script exits non-zero → run exits non-zero,
  partial run has stages {a} captured + valid (run show works, ParseJSON ok). Swap
  b's script for a passing one, `etude run <workflow> --resume <id>` → frontier=b,
  completes b,c; final manifest has a,b,c. Assert no duplicate stages, CAS chain
  intact. ALSO assert the resumed run's stage-a output blob AND the `task`-role input
  blob are byte-PRESENT in the post-resume commit (not merely referenced) — proves
  the referenced-paths blob-bytes reseed incl. the task input (opus). Manifest Stages
  are built explicitly from result bytes (record.go model), never derived from
  store.artifacts, so reseed-time AddContent cannot leak duplicate stage entries.
  ALSO test: `etude run show`/`list` reserved-name rejection; forward-replay
  single-stage-flag rejection; no-commit-repo clear error.
- AC4 chaining: assert stage b's recorded input ArtifactRef (role/sha) equals
  stage a's recorded output ArtifactRef (content-addressed identity) — i.e.
  output-role→input-role chaining matches capture-run semantics.
- Engine unit tests with replay.StubRunner (CONCAT/CANNED/Err modes) over a real
  refstore in a temp repo: incremental CAS sequence, create-only collision
  (ErrRefExists), stale-CAS abort, resume frontier derivation, runner resolution
  (inline vs seat-name vs default vs undefined-seat).

