### Risks
- Literal-AC vs description tension: bead description says "capture the failed
  stage's status", but ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA (read literally) require only
  resumability. I deliberately add NO manifest schema field for failed-stage
  status (an orchestration bead should not mutate the manifest schema; it would
  trip defect #5 round-trip scrutiny). Failure is surfaced via exit code + stderr;
  the partial run captures only successfully-completed stages. Flagging for the
  gate: if a recorded failed-stage marker is deemed required, it is a follow-up
  schema bead.
- LLM-stage replay substitution is deferred; v1 forward replay re-invokes runners,
  which is exact only for deterministic graphs (the proof). Stated explicitly so
  the gate scrutinizes the boundary rather than assuming full LLM-run replay.
- Worktree state not captured as artifacts won't survive replay; mitigated by the
  role-chaining contract (the deterministic proof passes ALL inter-stage data
  through captured roles).
- O(n) artifact-blob re-add per CAS commit (full-tree rewrite each step); blobs are
  content-addressed/idempotent and trees tiny — acceptable, noted.

